  "text": "Found 5 Go source files in grafana/grafana under pkg/components/loki/ that implement Loki client retry and timeout logic. HTTP transport: lokihttp/client.go implements HTTP retry with StopNow() to halt retries and context.WithTimeout() for per-request timeouts, lokihttp/config.go defines the BackoffConfig struct with MinBackoff/MaxBackoff/MaxRetries and the Timeout field for overall client timeout, lokihttp/fake.go provides a test stub implementing the same client interface with a no-op StopNow() method. gRPC transport: lokigrpc/client.go implements gRPC retry via grpcretry.WithMax() to limit retry attempts and uses context.WithTimeout() for per-call timeouts, lokigrpc/config.go defines the Retries field (used with grpcretry.WithMax) and Timeout field for the gRPC client configuration.",
